\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>As everyone settled into their seats, Evan stood apart, a mix of nerves and excitement palpable in his stance. He launched into his announcement with a mischievous grin, "Before we start lightening Guido's pockets, I had an epiphany after yet another uninspiring date. I've breakthrough idea I can\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t wait to share with all you!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Laughter filled the room as Evan's remark hit its mark, especially with Guido as the butt of the joke. Guido retorted with equal humor, "Well, prepare yourselves, folks. By the end of the night, it's your money that will be migrating to my pocket!"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The room was alive with light-hearted ribbing, but as the laughter died down, all eyes turned back to Evan. Joe, ever impatient for the poker to commence, was the sole exception, his eagerness barely contained. Evan, knowing the power of engagement, chose to preface his reveal with an interactive approach, sidestepping a monologue for a more captivating entry into his proposal.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan posed a thought-provoking question to the group, "What's the major pitfall in long-term relationships?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, ever the class clown, quipped, "<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>They end up hating each other.<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Alicia, unable to resist a dig at Guido's expense, retorted with a straight face, "\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What would you know? Your idea of a long-term relationship is a three-day weekend."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Her comment, though not intended to amuse, sent ripples of laughter through the room. Even Guido, usually quick to bounce back with a jest of his own, acknowledged the hit with a chuckle.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I gotta hand it to you, Alicia, that was a good one!\u8221\'94 Guido conceded with a chuckle, admiration in his tone.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Alicia, clearly not swayed by Guido's praise, turned her focus back to Evan, dismissing the interruption, "Ignore him, Evan. Let's hear this idea of yours."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, nodding at Guido's observation, added, "Well, 'hating' might be strong, but you're not entirely wrong."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 This acknowledgment drew a range of reactions: a smug smile from Guido, indifference from Joe, intrigue from Abe, and looks of astonishment from Liz and Alicia.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, leaning into the conversation with a gravity that quieted the room, shared his findings. "It is well known that the divorce rate in this country is over 50%. Think about it. In this room, only Joe\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s parents are still together. Liz and my parents divorced when we were young. Guido and Alicia were raised by single moms, and Abe\u8217\'92s parents divorced later in life.\u8221\'94 His voice trailed off, inviting contemplation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The room fell into a reflective silence, the weight of Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s words settling over the group like a heavy blanket. Everyone exchanged glances, acknowledging the truth in Evan's observation without words. As the moment stretched, they collectively turned back to Evan, their faces a mixture of curiosity and resignation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, sensing their attention fully back on him, pressed on, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I would estimate that 90% of all committed relationships end in a breakup or divorce.\u8221\'94 His statement, bold and a bit unsettling, hung in the air.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, ever the optimist and perhaps a bit defensive about the sanctity of relationships, couldn't help but challenge him. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, that\u8217\'92s nonsense. 90%? Really?\u8221\'94 Disbelief tinged her voice, her eyebrows arching in skepticism.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Unfazed, Evan leaned into his argument further, a rhetorical question at the ready. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Can anyone guess how many people are registered on dating or hookup sites?\u8221\'94 His gaze swept the room, inviting speculation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, slightly irked by the direction of the conversation but engaged nonetheless, ventured a guess. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t know, Evan - a million?\u8221\'94 Her tone was a mix of irritation and curiosity, a testament to her relationship with her brother.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, eager to share his findings and perhaps sway his sister's opinion, corrected her with emphasis, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Conservatively, tens and tens and tens of millions.\u8221\'94 He repeated 'tens' for emphasis, his eyes alight with the thrill of revelation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, still struggling to wrap her mind around the figures, expressed her skepticism. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That can\u8217\'92t be right.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 But Evan stood firm, bolstered by his research. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s true, I researched it last night.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, voiced his admiration. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My boy did his homework!\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, not missing a beat, continued with his train of thought, leaning forward for emphasis. "With a few cringy exceptions, that means, like me, those tens of millions of website members have a 100% failure rate." His statement, bold and a bit unsettling, seemed to echo in the quiet of the room.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Abe, nodded thoughtfully. "I think you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re right about that, Evan. I often hear the students at the University discussing their experiences with online dating. I would venture to guess that if you polled the students in my classes, the vast majority are currently or were recently members of a dating site.\u8221\'94 His deep voice carried the weight of experience, lending credibility to Evan's argument.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, visibly buoyed by Abe's agreement, grew more animated. "Exactly! And that doesn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t even count the number of single people not using the web to find a partner.\u8221\'94 His eyes sparkled with the excitement of sharing his insights, his hands gesturing broadly to encompass the gravity of his statement.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, unable to resist injecting his own brand of humor into the conversation, quipped with a smirk, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I have a feeling we have some more stats coming our way!\u8221\'94 His comment, though made in jest, acknowledged Evan's characteristic thoroughness and penchant for detail.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, momentarily pausing to scratch his head in a display of mock contemplation, sighed. "When I think about all the couples I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve known over the years, it feels like half of them aren\u8217\'92t exactly living the dream. They stay together for the kids, convenience, financial concerns, or dread the idea of starting over. That leaves only 5% of relationships that I would consider healthy.\u8221\'94 His voice trailed off, a hint of sadness tinging his words as he contemplated the state of modern relationships.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, feeling a mix of defensiveness and pride, couldn't help but respond. "What about the couples in this room? Our relationships are thriving!\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Her tone carried a note of challenge, a testament to her belief in the strength of the bonds around her. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, navigating the delicate balance of his next words, offered a gentle disclaimer. "I agree. I don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t want to offend anyone, but I can\u8217\'92t think of even one long-term relationship with energy matching levels when the relationship began. Most relationships peak within their first year." He hesitated, a thoughtful look crossing his face, aware that Liz was on the edge of her seat, perhaps ready to counter his next words. Sensing the tension, he decided not to dive deeper into the potentially contentious part of his theory.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Shifting his gaze to the distance, Evan's expression softened, a dreamlike quality entering his voice. "There\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s nothing quite like the first magical year getting to know someone. A time where everything feels fresh - the first kiss, the excitement of holding hands, the initial rush of exploring intimacy together, discovering new places to eat, maybe even that first trip away." He paused, lost for a moment in the reminiscence of such times, a wistful smile playing at the corners of his mouth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 But the mood shifted as Evan's voice took on a somber tone, his gaze lowering to the floor. "But then, over time, everything shifts. It's like couples just stop trying. The spark goes out, they argue more, and that thrill of seeing each other fades away, sometimes disappearing entirely. Next thing you know, they are breaking up, signing divorce papers, and ending up with..." He trailed off, the weight of the words too heavy, before lifting his eyes to meet those of his audience. "...a whole lot of heartache." The room hung on his every word, a collective empathy in the air. "Even the best of couples can't seem to keep up the energy from their first year together." The reality of his statement seemed to settle over the room, a mix of agreement and contemplation in the eyes of his family and friends.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Alicia leaned in, her voice carrying the weight of wisdom and personal experience. "Let's not forget, Evan, everyone's love story is unique. Abe and I, we might not be all over each other like we just met, but our connection runs deep, built on respect. That includes respecting the long hours and the sacrifices we both make for our careers." Her words, sincere and heartfelt, resonated in the room, offering a different perspective on love.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Abe, always the philosopher, shared his thoughts with a calm, measured tone. "Evan, I've listened with an open mind, and you make some compelling points. However, trying to keep life at a perpetual climax? That's a puzzle no one can solve. Humans, like all creatures, aren't meant for endless peaks.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 His words, steeped in wisdom, seemed to echo through the room, challenging Evan's premise with gentle authority.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, caught in a moment of self-reflection, sighed deeply, a mix of frustration and resignation in her voice. "I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92m ashamed to admit it, but Joe and I have let things slide between us far too often. After a grueling day, it's too tempting to just veg out. We end up ordering in and binge-watching instead of really connecting with each other." Her admission, raw and honest, struck a chord with everyone present.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, his voice tinged with regret, quickly reassured his sister. "Liz, I didn't mean to make anyone feel bad, least of all you." His words were sincere, a brother's concern breaking through the tension of the conversation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, her tone softening, acknowledged Evan's intention. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I get it, you weren't pointing fingers. Yes, that early thrill of a new relationship has settled down with Joe and me. But it's been replaced by something so much stronger. My relationship with Joe is rooted in the only thing that counts - love. These roots run deep and are strong, not only because of life's greatest joys, but also because of life\u8217\'92s toughest challenges. With all your talk of numbers and percentages, you have left love out of the equation." Her words were a testament to the depth of her commitment, a beacon of hope amidst Evan's bleak outlook.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, the hurt visible in his eyes and body language, responded with a voice laced with resignation. "I didn't factor in love because, for me, love's off the table. You get one shot at true love. I had mine, and now it's lost forever." The room fell into a stunned silence, the palpable pain of Evan's admission leaving a heavy air of sympathy and concern.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, moved by her brother's vulnerability, wrapped him in a warm hug before stepping back, her eyes shining with care and love. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re young, wonderful, and handsome. Love will find its way back to you.\u8221\'94 Her words, filled with hope and belief, sought to mend the cracks in Evan's broken heart, reminding him and everyone present that love, in its many forms, remains an unyielding force.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
