\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Raising his voice to ensure he was heard, Evan called out,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs30\cf1  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"Hey, Joe."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs30\cf1  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Joe glanced up from the deck of cards he was shuffling. With Joe's full attention, Evan posed a pointed question.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs30\cf1  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"Joe, is there a backup plan for love if things go south with Liz?"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Joe didn't hesitate, his reply ringing with conviction.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f3\fs22\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::0> <!$Scr_Cs::0>}{\f2\fs22\b1\i0\cf9 <$Scr_Cs::3>"<!$Scr_Cs::3>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>Not a chance! Liz is my everything. There's no one else for me."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan turned back to Liz, pressing on,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And Liz, if you and Joe didn't make it, is there someone else who could take his place?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Liz, clearly agitated by Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s line of questioning, responded,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs30\cf1  }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, that\u8217\'92s not fair to ask.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan stood firm, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s the fairest question of all. Look around; the couples in this room found their once-in-a-lifetime love and clung to it. If I still had my true love, I\u8217\'92d be content with those quiet nights in, embracing every high and low life throws at us, as long as we faced it together.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Liz felt a rare irritation bubbling up.  It was unusual for Evan to counter every suggestion she made with such persistence. His readiness to challenge her at every turn was both surprising and unsettling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Alicia, noticing the tension building in Liz, sought to steer the discussion in a more productive direction:<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, what\u8217\'92s the endpoint of all this? You mentioned having an epiphany that sparked a brilliant idea?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Alicia's intervention proved effective, pulling Evan back from the brink of despondency. Revitalized, the initial zeal with which Evan began the discussion made a comeback, signaling he was primed to divulge both his revelation and his novel approach to relationships.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan, his voice gaining the cadence of a seasoned storyteller, began, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, there I was, driving home last night, just glad to have the date behind me. Yet, I couldn't help but replay every moment of it in my head. The woman I was with? She was undeniably attractive, intelligent, and had a great sense of humor. Despite her being practically perfect, the thought of a second date didn't even cross my mind.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Guido chimed in with his trademark blend of jest and a sliver of sincerity,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I'll happily take her off your hands. Shoot me her number, will ya?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Alicia, seizing the moment to land a playful jab at Guido, retorted, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"Dream on, Guido. She's way out of your league. Remember, Evan mentioned she's intelligent." <!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>The room erupted in laughter, marking the second time Alicia's quick wit won the crowd over.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, conceding with a grin, acknowledged,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I've got to hand it to you, Alicia. You're really on fire tonight!\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan, steering the conversation back to his revelation, continued,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Reflecting on the countless dates from the past year, I realized something. While a few were outright disasters and others simply fell flat, the majority involved decent women. And yet, I couldn't bring myself to see them again. It was during this reflection I had my epiphany. Deep down, I knew these relationships were doomed to fail or become unsatisfying.  More significantly, I finally accepted the fact that there was zero chance the relationship would result in true love.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Liz, her voice laced with concern and a hint of desperation for Evan to view things from a brighter perspective, softly exclaimed, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, Evan.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Abe, unexpectedly finding himself drawn into Evan's narrative, inquired with genuine interest, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, what groundbreaking idea did this epiphany lead to?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan, unable to contain his anticipation, began energetically rubbing his hands together as if to warm up for the grand finale. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"I'm glad you asked,"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1> he said, a spark of excitement lighting his eyes. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"After coming to terms with the impossibility of ever finding true love again, it dawned on me that there might be another way to capture something just as fulfilling!"<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Alicia leaned forward, intrigued. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>"And what's this 'next best thing'?" <!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Grinning from ear to ear, Evan dove right in. "<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>Well, since dating's been a bust and finding 'the one' a second time is nothing more than a fairytale, I thought of something kinda out there. Why not find someone cool? Not just a pretty face, but someone I would like hanging out with. Since relationships are often all fireworks in the first year, why not make a deal to just enjoy that ride for a year? Then, when the year is over, call it quits while things are still good, avoiding all that mess when things start to go downhill."<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>With his idea now fully revealed, Evan's gaze swept across the room, searching for a hint of shared excitement. Instead, he was met with expressions ranging from perplexed to utterly astonished. Notably, Liz's reaction was the most striking to Evan; her features frozen in a state of sheer astonishment, far exceeding simple surprise or disbelief.}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, her voice laced with incredulity, couldn't mask her disbelief.  <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Let me get this straight. Your grand scheme is to date a girl for a year and then dump her? What girl is going to go for that?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan, feeling his intentions were being misconstrued, clarified,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It's not about 'dating' for a year, Liz. It\u8217\'92s about sharing a meaningful relationship for that time. But yes, finding someone agreeable to such a proposition might be a challenge.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Alicia, chiming in with a dose of reality, pointed out, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Evan, any woman worth spending a year with isn\u8217\'92t going to sign up for an expiration date on the relationship.\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan conceded,<!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re right, Alicia. Which is why I couldn\u8217\'92t disclose the full scope of my plan upfront. Besides, it could tarnish the Vaughn Foundation's reputation if it ever got out that I\u8217\'92m that I am going around asking women to be in relationship of this kind.\u8221\'94 <!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Liz couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help but respond with a hint of sarcasm, <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2>\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You think?\u8221\'94<!$Scr_Cs::2>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>Evan leaned forward, a crease of concern etching his brow as he grappled with the ethical dilemma of his plan. "I don't feel great about not being able to disclose my plan upfront," he confessed, his voice tinged with unease. "But, I think I've found a way to compensate for the deceit and the hurt that an unexpected breakup might cause."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz raised an eyebrow, skepticism shadowing her features. "And how do you propose to manage that?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan met her gaze, his expression earnest, a spark of hope flickering in his eyes. "Abe made a great point about people not being meant to live at constant emotional highs. Considering it's just for a year, I plan to be 'the perfect boyfriend'\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 attentive, caring, supportive, ensuring her every need is met. I know that's something I can commit to for a year."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz folded her arms, unconvinced. "So, you believe being Mr. Perfect for a year makes up for the heartbreak of a blindside breakup?" she challenged, her voice rising slightly.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan nodded, his conviction not faltering. "Yes, I genuinely believe that. If a woman were to truly consider it, I think many would accept a moment of heartache in exchange for a year of being treated well," he reasoned, trying to gauge his sister's reaction.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, her affection for her brother evident despite her opposition to his plan, placed a comforting hand on his shoulder. "Evan, you're my brother, and I understand this is coming from a place of pain and loneliness," she said softly, her voice imbued with warmth yet firm with resolve. "But I cannot, in good conscience, stand by and watch you go through with such an ridiculous plan."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, unable to remain a mere spectator any longer. "Look, Evan's approach might be a bit out there, but calling it ridiculous? That's a stretch."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, eyebrows knitted in confusion and disbelief, turned to Guido. "How on earth can you defend this? Even if I wanted to support him, there's no way this plan could ever succeed. Evan, you're the despise lying and you\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re bad at it. Any woman would see right through this in a heartbeat."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan massaged his temples. "I've been wrestling with this idea, thinking it through from every angle. Then It dawned on me, I wouldn't have to lie <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f0\fs26\b0 per se\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 just avoid revealing my plan the breakup after a year.}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, shaking her head in disapproval: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on, Evan. You know better than that. The whole relationship would be one big lie.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 The weight of Liz's disappointment was a tangible force, pressing uncomfortably against Evan's chest. He knew she was right, yet admitting his desperation wasn't something he was prepared to do\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not here, not in front of everyone. He struggled internally, his thoughts a whirlwind. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}{\f6\fs26\i1\cf11 <$Scr_Cs::4>But Liz, I'm at my wit's end. Do I become like Guido, hopping from one bed to another? I'm done with dating; it's just not for me. What choices do I have left? Resign myself to solitude or go ahead with this plan?<!$Scr_Cs::4>}
\par\pard\plain \sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 Seeing Evan struggle, Guido stepped in to support his friend: "Liz, I think you're being a bit harsh. Everybody holds back something in a relationship \endash  especially at the beginning.  The dating world is all about people presenting their best selves, not their real selves. }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s not planning to lie; he\u8217\'92s just focusing on being the best partner he can be. }{\f0\fs26\b0 Not because he has to, but because he wants to. That's is Evan's real self and there is no lie in that.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Liz, her voice laced with concern and a softening demeanor, responded: "But can't you see how that will make it harder on the poor girl? She\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ll be left heartbroken, wondering why everything so  perfect ended so suddenly."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Guido, never one to shy away from a debate\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 even with Liz, whom he respected deeply\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 countered: }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So what you're saying, Liz, is that Evan will never find true love again?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Liz was caught off guard by Guido's response }{The air was thick with puzzled glances, leaving the room in a rare state of perplexed silence as }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 everyone, including Evan, pondered the underlying message in Guido's challenge.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Alicia, visibly upset and rising to Liz's defense, snapped: "He didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t say that, Guido! Don\u8217\'92t twist her words.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Guido, with a hint of mischief yet making a point, retorted: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m just going by what I heard. It seemed pretty clear to me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, trying to keep the peace, interjected: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Calm down you two. Guido, why would you think I'm saying Evan's never gonna find true love again?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Guido leaned in, his voice laced with conviction, "You're assuming it'll end in a breakup after a year, right?" }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Liz, perplexed yet intrigued by where Guido was leading, nodded, "That's the plan, isn't it?" }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 As the conversation unfolded, Guido shared his perspective on the unpredictable nature of relationships, emphasizing that every love story begins shrouded in uncertainty. He posited that even the most thought-out plans for a relationship seldom pan out as expected. }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 Guido suggested to Liz that Evan would probably fall in love with the first girl he tried this relationship plan with and a breakup would likely never happen. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0 Evan was irked by Guido's suggestion, }{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 <$Scr_Cs::4>Guido's nuts, I'm never going to fall in love again.<!$Scr_Cs::4>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 <$Scr_Cs::2> <!$Scr_Cs::2>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 Evan's annoyance with Guido's claims gave way to feeling }{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 a flicker of hope as he noticed Liz's expression soften}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0\cf8 .}{\f6\fs26\b0\i1\cf11 <$Scr_Cs::4> Look at Liz's face! Is she finally starting to come around? <!$Scr_Cs::4>}{\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>This hint of acceptance from Liz introduced a sliver of hope to Evan's rigid outlook, suggesting that the path of his planned relationship might not be as predetermined as he thought. <!$Scr_Cs::1>}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Evan (Seeing a crack in Liz's armor, he decided to run with it): \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, Liz. If there is a chance I might find love again, isn\u8217\'92t this a better way than what I\u8217\'92ve been doing the last year? Either I\u8217\'92m going to find a woman I love and want to spend the rest of my life with, or I will have a wonderful relationship for a year that would end in a breakup regardless. Come on, sis. Back me on this. I really need your support.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Liz, think about it. If there's even the smallest chance I could stumble upon love again, wouldn't this approach be better than the endless string of go-nowhere dates? It's either I discover someone to grow old with, or I enjoy a year of something meaningful before it inevitably ends. I need you in my corner on this one. Can't you see it's worth a shot?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz's response was a contemplative silence, her thoughts evidently churning.}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\sa120\sl264\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 <$Scr_Cs::1>In Liz's silence, Evan saw a crack in the armor and turned up the sibling charm. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Liz, I'm begging here. I really think this could be good for me. I can't do this without your support. Please, for your baby brother?\u8221\'94 He urged, his child-like smile disarmingly sweet.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Liz, wordless, simply stood and retreated to another room, leaving Evan hanging in a suspenseful silence, wondering if his plea had reached her heart or if he'd pushed too far.<!$Scr_Cs::1>}
